$ ADODB.Command: CreateParameter
@ createParameter

The `createParameter` function of the `→ development/databases/ADO/objects/command` creates a `→ development/databases/ADO/objects/parameter` object.

{ Arguments

  table { ll

    `name` ☰ A `→ development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/string` value that contains the name of the `→ development/databases/ADO/objects/parameter` object.
    `type` ☰ A → development/databases/ADO/data-types#ado-dataTypeEnum[`dataTypeEnum`] value that specifies the data type of the `→ development/databases/ADO/objects/parameter` object.
    `direction` ☰ A `parameterDirectionEnum` value that specifies the type of the `→ development/databases/ADO/objects/parameter` object.
    `size` ☰ A `→ development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/long` value that specifies the maximum length for the parameter value in characters or bytes.
    `value` ☰ A `→ development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant` that specifies the value for the `→ development/databases/ADO/objects/parameter` object.

  table }

  All arguments are optional.

}
